            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01MZhgwF2W4qdqowDzyre4Aa\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_014oiefjYwjBMJLAFJ9qfQd4\",\"name\":\"extract\",\"input\":{\"text\":\"I hear the passion — that's real! But here's what I'm noticing: we've drifted pretty far from a business idea. \\\"Pasta is so good it makes me want to die\\\" is a personal feeling, not a business model or problem you're solving.\\n\\nLet me be direct: **What's the actual business here?** Are you:\\n- Starting a pasta company or restaurant?\\n- Building a pasta-focused content platform (blog, YouTube, podcast)?\\n- Creating a service around pasta (delivery, cooking classes, community)?\\n- Something else entirely?\\n\\nI ask because we started with Friend of the Pod — a real, specific business idea. Then pasta came up. I want to make sure we're not avoiding the hard work of defining what you actually *do*, or if you've genuinely pivoted to something pasta-related and we need to start fresh there.\\n\\nEither way, I'm here to help. But I need you to give me something I can work with — a real problem, a real audience, a real solution.\",\"examples\":[\"I'm launching a pasta brand and want to use podcasts to reach food enthusiasts\",\"I'm building a community platform where pasta lovers can share recipes and connect\",\"I'm creating an online cooking school focused on authentic Italian pasta-making\"],\"conclusion\":\"Your enthusiasm is genuine — that's the foundation of something good. But right now, we need to translate that into a business idea we can actually market. What's the real thing you want to build?\"}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2187,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":377,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
