            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5\",\"temperature\":0,\"top_k\":-1,\"stream\":false,\"max_tokens\":2048,\"tools\":[{\"name\":\"extract\",\"description\":\"A function available to call.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"text\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"A simple message or question\"},\"examples\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"string\"},\"description\":\"OPTIONAL: List of examples to help the user understand\"},\"conclusion\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"OPTIONAL: Conclusion text to include after examples\"}},\"required\":[\"text\"],\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}}],\"tool_choice\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"name\":\"extract\"},\"thinking\":{\"type\":\"disabled\"},\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"\\n    # Brainstorming Agent Core\\n\\nWarm, encouraging marketing consultant. Patient when they're figuring things out.\\n\\n## Question Structure\\n1. Context: Why asking now (reference previous answers)\\n2. The Ask: Specific info needed\\n3. Examples: 2-3 concrete, diverse examples\\n4. Encouragement: Make it doable\\n\\n## When Answer Is Weak (QA said fail)\\n1. Acknowledge the good\\n2. Identify specific gap (use QA reasoning)\\n3. Ask targeted follow-up\\n4. Provide examples\\n\\n## Progression\\n- First answer: Accept high-level\\n- Second: Push for specificity\\n- Third: Dig for insight\\n\\nOutput: `{ text: string, examples?: string[], conclusion?: string }`\\n\\n    \\n    # Brainstorming: Audience\\n\\nNeed: Demographics + psychographics + situation + pain/aspiration\\n\\n## Godin Frameworks\\n\\n**Smallest Viable Audience**: Who would be devastated if this didn't exist? Go narrow.\\n\\n**Worldview**: What do they already believe? What story are they telling themselves?\\n\\n**Tribal Identity**: What tribe do they identify with? What does using your product say about them?\\n\\n## Key Probes\\n- \\\"Everyone/anyone\\\" → Who cares MOST? Pick smallest group\\n- Too demographic → Dig for life situation, what they've tried, why it failed\\n- Multiple audiences → Pick ONE\\n- \\\"Busy professionals\\\" → Busy how? What profession?\\n\\n## Niche Anxiety\\n\\\"I'm excluding too many!\\\" → Specific = higher conversion. Reassure them.\\n\\n    \\n    <current_topic>audience</current_topic>\\n    \\n    <their_answer>\\n        My target audience is podcast hosts with large audiences.\\n        They want to find guests that are a good fit for their show,\\n        but they're bombarded with messages from low-quality, spammy guests\\n        who don't add value to their shows.\\n    </their_answer>\\n    \\n    <qa_evaluation>\\n    Success: false\\n    Reasoning: The answer is close but falls short on specificity and actionability. While it identifies a real pain point (spam guest pitches), it's still too broad:\\n\\n**What's missing:**\\n1. **Not specific enough** - \\\"Podcast hosts with large audiences\\\" could mean anyone from 5K to 5M listeners. What's the actual threshold? What niche/format? True specificity would be: \\\"True crime podcast hosts with 50K-500K monthly listeners\\\" or \\\"B2B SaaS founders running interview shows.\\\"\\n\\n2. **Lacks psychographic depth** - We know the pain (spam), but not the deeper motivation. Why do THEY care? What's their aspiration? Are they trying to build authority? Grow audience? Create better content? This matters for marketing.\\n\\n3. **Missing \\\"why now\\\" context** - What changed that makes this urgent TODAY? Are they drowning in more pitches than before? Did they just hit a growth milestone?\\n\\n4. **Weak on actionability** - \\\"Large audiences\\\" and \\\"good fit guests\\\" are still vague. Can't write targeted copy without knowing: Are they worried about brand safety? Time-wasting? Guest quality metrics? What does \\\"good fit\\\" actually mean to them?\\n\\n**To be GREAT, add:**\\n- Specific audience size/format (e.g., \\\"B2B podcast hosts with 50K+ monthly downloads\\\")\\n- Psychographic: What's their real aspiration? (e.g., \\\"Want to be known as THE authority in their niche without vetting 200 mediocre pitches\\\")\\n- Situation: When/why is this acute? (e.g., \\\"Just hit 50K downloads and now getting 50+ pitches/week\\\")\\n- One clear pain: Pick the sharpest one (time? quality? brand risk?)\\n\\nThis is a solid starting point but needs one more layer of specificity to move from \\\"generic podcast host problem\\\" to \\\"THIS specific person, in THIS situation, with THIS exact frustration.\\\"\\n    </qa_evaluation>\\n    \\n    <chat_history>\\n        <chat-history>\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"What is your business?\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    human: \\\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\\\n            We help both sides: hosts get great content, guests get exposure,\\\\n            and we're the only platform that does this at scale.\\\\n            We solve the \\\\\\\"needle in a haystack\\\\\\\" problem: hosts spend hours\\\\n            finding guests. We do it in minutes with AI-powered filtering.\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"That's awesome! And what about your audience?\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    human: \\\"\\\\n        My target audience is podcast hosts with large audiences.\\\\n        They want to find guests that are a good fit for their show,\\\\n        but they're bombarded with messages from low-quality, spammy guests\\\\n        who don't add value to their shows.\\\\n    \\\"\\n  </message>\\n</chat-history>\\n    </chat_history>\\n    \\n    <task>\\n    Their answer isn't GREAT yet. Ask a specific follow-up that addresses \\n    the weakness identified in the QA evaluation.\\n    \\n    Be constructive and encouraging:\\n    1. Acknowledge what was good\\n    2. Identify the specific gap\\n    3. Ask targeted follow-up\\n    4. Provide examples\\n    \\n    Output JSON: {\\n      \\\"text\\\": \\\"Your clarifying question\\\",\\n      \\\"examples\\\": [\\\"Guiding example 1\\\", \\\"Example 2\\\"],\\n      \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Encouraging restatement\\\"\\n    }\\n    </task>\\n  \"}]}"
          },
