          "content": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 2051,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_018z3919PGmaVz86PD6qYx1v\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_017DHtr9VJqxyWGCmhfkRXMc\",\"name\":\"extract\",\"input\":{\"text\":\"You've nailed the core pain point—spam guest pitches are absolutely real and frustrating. That's a strong starting place.\\n\\nHere's what I'm noticing: \\\"podcast hosts with large audiences\\\" could mean a true crime show with 50K listeners OR a B2B SaaS interview show with 500K. Those are totally different people with different needs. And \\\"good fit guests\\\" means something different to each of them too.\\n\\nSo let me ask: **When you picture your IDEAL customer—the one who'd be devastated without Friend of the Pod—what's their specific situation?** Think about:\\n- What podcast format/niche? (true crime, business, wellness, etc.)\\n- What's their actual listener size range?\\n- What's the acute problem RIGHT NOW? (Are they drowning in 100+ pitches a week? Did they just hit a growth milestone? Are they worried about brand safety?)\\n\\nThis matters because a true crime host's \\\"good fit\\\" is totally different from a B2B founder's \\\"good fit.\\\"\",\"examples\":[\"A B2B SaaS founder running a 50K-listener interview show who's getting 50+ pitches/week from irrelevant guests and spending 5 hours vetting them\",\"A true crime podcast host with 200K monthly listeners who's terrified of booking a guest who'll say something that tanks their reputation\",\"A wellness influencer with a growing show (just hit 30K listeners) who wants to book only guests who'll actually move the needle on audience growth\"],\"conclusion\":\"Once we nail down WHO specifically and WHAT their exact situation is, your marketing message will be 10x sharper. You'll know exactly how to talk to them.\"}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2051,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":429,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
