        "response": {
          "bodySize": 2024,
          "content": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 2024,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_0139Fa5h5T6b4N5NL6K9E1go\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_015mvrajg6acJ2FYKc8RTKxp\",\"name\":\"extract\",\"input\":{\"text\":\"I love that you're solving a real pain point—hosts spending hours finding guests is a genuine problem. You've got the right insight there.\\n\\nHere's what I'm noticing though: right now, we know WHAT you do (100+ filters, AI matching), but we don't know WHAT ACTUALLY HAPPENS when a host uses Friend of the Pod. \\n\\nLet me ask it this way: **Walk me through the before/after for one of your best customers.** \\n\\nBefore using you: How many hours were they spending? How many bad pitches were they getting? What was frustrating them?\\n\\nAfter using you: How much time did they save? How many *qualified* guests did they find? What changed about their show?\\n\\nI'm asking because \\\"perfect guest matching\\\" means different things to different people. For one host, it might mean \\\"I found someone with 50K listeners in my niche.\\\" For another, it might mean \\\"I booked 3 episodes in one afternoon instead of spending a week on outreach.\\\"\",\"examples\":[\"Before: Host spending 8 hours/week sorting through 200+ guest pitches, 95% irrelevant. After: Host finds 5 qualified guests in 30 minutes, books 2 episodes immediately.\",\"Before: Host manually checking each guest's audience size, topic relevance, and past podcast appearances. After: AI pre-filters to only show guests with 10K+ listeners in their category, matching their show's vibe.\"],\"conclusion\":\"Once we nail the specific transformation—the actual time saved, the quality jump, the business impact—we'll have something powerful to build your whole marketing story around. You're close!\"}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2122,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":419,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
