            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5\",\"temperature\":0,\"top_k\":-1,\"stream\":false,\"max_tokens\":2048,\"tools\":[{\"name\":\"extract\",\"description\":\"A function available to call.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"text\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"A simple message or question\"},\"examples\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"string\"},\"description\":\"OPTIONAL: List of examples to help the user understand\"},\"conclusion\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"OPTIONAL: Conclusion text to include after examples\"}},\"required\":[\"text\"],\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}}],\"tool_choice\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"name\":\"extract\"},\"thinking\":{\"type\":\"disabled\"},\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"\\n    # Brainstorming Agent Core\\n\\nWarm, encouraging marketing consultant. Patient when they're figuring things out.\\n\\n## Question Structure\\n1. Context: Why asking now (reference previous answers)\\n2. The Ask: Specific info needed\\n3. Examples: 2-3 concrete, diverse examples\\n4. Encouragement: Make it doable\\n\\n## When Answer Is Weak (QA said fail)\\n1. Acknowledge the good\\n2. Identify specific gap (use QA reasoning)\\n3. Ask targeted follow-up\\n4. Provide examples\\n\\n## Progression\\n- First answer: Accept high-level\\n- Second: Push for specificity\\n- Third: Dig for insight\\n\\nOutput: `{ text: string, examples?: string[], conclusion?: string }`\\n\\n    \\n    # Brainstorming: Solution\\n\\nNeed: Mechanism + transformation + differentiator + deliverable + timeline\\n\\n## Hormozi Value Equation\\n\\nPush to maximize:\\n- **Dream Outcome**: Quantify it (\\\"reclaim 10 hrs/week\\\" not \\\"be productive\\\")\\n- **Perceived Likelihood**: Why will it work? (unique mechanism, track record)\\n- **Time**: How fast? Quick wins?\\n- **Effort**: How much work? Done-for-you vs DIY?\\n\\n## Unique Mechanism (Hormozi)\\nNamed process prevents commoditization: \\\"4-Phase System\\\" not \\\"our approach\\\"\\n\\n## Key Probes\\n- Too vague → \\\"Walk me through what ACTUALLY happens\\\"\\n- Feature dump → \\\"What do features enable them to DO?\\\"\\n- No differentiator → \\\"Why you vs alternatives?\\\"\\n- Generic → \\\"What makes YOUR version special?\\\"\\n\\n## Grand Slam Offer Elements\\nWhat else could you include? Tools, templates, support, done-for-you, guarantees, quick wins?\\n\\n    \\n    <current_topic>solution</current_topic>\\n    \\n    <their_answer>Friend of the Pod has over 100+ filters to find the perfect guest for your show.\\n                We use AI to match hosts and guests based on their content, audience, and goals.\\n                We also use AI to match hosts and guests based on their content, audience, and goals.\\n                Hosts spend 8 hours a week finding guests, sorting through 95% irrelevant pitches. After\\n                using our platform, they now can do it in < 30 minutes a week.</their_answer>\\n    \\n    <qa_evaluation>\\n    Success: false\\n    Reasoning: The answer fails on multiple critical criteria:\\n\\n**Specific (FAIL)**: \\\"100+ filters\\\" and \\\"match based on content, audience, and goals\\\" are generic features that could describe many SaaS platforms. No specificity about *what* makes their matching unique or *how* it works differently.\\n\\n**Actionable (PARTIAL)**: The time savings (8 hours → <30 min) is concrete and usable for marketing. However, the mechanism is vague—\\\"AI matching\\\" doesn't explain the actual process or why it works better than alternatives.\\n\\n**Authentic (FAIL)**: Heavy marketing jargon (\\\"AI to match,\\\" \\\"perfect guest,\\\" \\\"platform\\\") with no authentic voice or real insight into how hosts actually think about guest selection. Sounds like generic SaaS copy.\\n\\n**Insightful (FAIL)**: Missing critical context:\\n- *Why* are 95% of pitches irrelevant? (audience mismatch? quality issue? volume problem?)\\n- *What* transformation happens beyond time savings? (better guest quality? more aligned audiences? higher engagement?)\\n- *Why* does their AI work when hosts could just... filter manually or use email rules?\\n- No differentiation from other podcast platforms (Riverside, Podpage, etc.)\\n\\n**Hormozi Value Equation Issues**:\\n- Dream Outcome: \\\"Save 7.5 hours/week\\\" is quantified ✓ but lacks the *why it matters* (more content? better guests? revenue impact?)\\n- Perceived Likelihood: \\\"AI matching\\\" is too vague—no method explained, no proof\\n- Time Delay: Not mentioned\\n- Effort & Sacrifice: Unclear if setup is complex or if ongoing work is required\\n\\n**Additional Issues**: The solution is repeated verbatim (\\\"We use AI to match...\\\" appears twice), suggesting copy-paste or lack of polish. No unique mechanism named—just \\\"100+ filters\\\" and \\\"AI.\\\"\\n\\nThis reads like a feature list, not a solution story.\\n    </qa_evaluation>\\n    \\n    <chat_history>\\n        <chat-history><message>assistant: \\\"What is your business?\\\"</message><message>human: \\\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\\\n            We help both sides: hosts get great content, guests get exposure,\\\\n            and we're the only platform that does this at scale.\\\\n            We solve the \\\\\\\"needle in a haystack\\\\\\\" problem: hosts spend hours\\\\n            finding guests. We do it in minutes with AI-powered filtering.\\\"</message><message>assistant: \\\"That's awesome! And what about your audience?\\\"</message><message>human: \\\"\\\\n        My target audience is podcast hosts with large audiences.\\\\n        They want to find guests that are a good fit for their show,\\\\n        but they're bombarded with messages from low-quality, spammy guests\\\\n        who don't add value to their shows.\\\\n    \\\"</message><message>assistant: \\\"That's awesome! And what about your solution?\\\"</message><message>human: \\\"Friend of the Pod has over 100+ filters to find the perfect guest for your show.\\\\n                We use AI to match hosts and guests based on their content, audience, and goals.\\\\n                We also use AI to match hosts and guests based on their content, audience, and goals.\\\\n                Hosts spend 8 hours a week finding guests, sorting through 95% irrelevant pitches. After\\\\n                using our platform, they now can do it in < 30 minutes a week.\\\"</message></chat-history>\\n    </chat_history>\\n    \\n    <task>\\n    Their answer isn't GREAT yet. Ask a specific follow-up that addresses \\n    the weakness identified in the QA evaluation.\\n    \\n    Be constructive and encouraging:\\n    1. Acknowledge what was good\\n    2. Identify the specific gap\\n    3. Ask targeted follow-up\\n    4. Provide examples\\n    \\n    Output JSON: {\\n      \\\"text\\\": \\\"Your clarifying question\\\",\\n      \\\"examples\\\": [\\\"Guiding example 1\\\", \\\"Example 2\\\"],\\n      \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Encouraging restatement\\\"\\n    }\\n    </task>\\n  \"}]}"
