            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 1955,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_017Vr71mQkHrey9BPJhBT534\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01M8tyKqTDLnUzo1uuvMLmPM\",\"name\":\"extract\",\"input\":{\"text\":\"I love that you've built something that actually solves a real pain—hosts ARE drowning in low-quality pitches. And the proprietary model trained on successful messages? That's a genuine differentiator.\\n\\nHere's what I'm sensing though: we know WHAT you filter, but we don't know WHAT HAPPENS NEXT or what actually changes for the host's business.\\n\\nLet me ask it this way: **Walk me through what a host actually experiences and gets as a result.** Not the features—the real outcome.\\n\\nFor example:\\n- \\\"A host logs in, sees 5 pre-screened guest options that match their audience, and books 2 of them within 30 minutes—guests who drive 15% higher engagement than their typical episodes\\\"\\n- \\\"Instead of spending 6 hours a week sorting through 200 pitches, the host now spends 15 minutes reviewing our curated list and has 3 confirmed guests ready to record\\\"\\n\\nWhat's the transformation for THEM? How much time do they reclaim? How many quality guests do they actually book? What does their show look like after using Friend of the Pod?\",\"examples\":[\"A host books 4-5 qualified guests per month (vs. 1-2 before) in under 20 minutes of work\",\"Hosts report 40% higher listener engagement on guest episodes because the matches are so precise\",\"The host goes from 'hoping' a guest fits to 'knowing' they'll resonate with their audience before they even pitch\"],\"conclusion\":\"You've got the mechanism—now let's crystallize the RESULT. That's what makes this irresistible.\"}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2273,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_token