            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 2295,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01EudSra4wfuPMT4FuLq95Kq\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01C828bjvWL2SkTxhBAbMKXu\",\"name\":\"extract\",\"input\":{\"text\":\"I love that you've identified the core pain—hosts drowning in low-quality pitches—and you've got a real differentiator with those proprietary models trained on successful messages. That's genuinely smart.\\n\\nBut here's what I'm noticing: we know WHAT you filter, but we don't know WHAT ACTUALLY CHANGES for the host. Right now it sounds like \\\"we remove bad pitches,\\\" but I need to understand the real transformation.\\n\\nWalk me through this: After a host uses Friend of the Pod, what's different about their week? How much time do they actually reclaim? What does \\\"perfect guest\\\" actually mean to them—is it someone who drives downloads? Fits their audience? Brings credibility?\\n\\nThe reason I'm asking is that \\\"100+ filters\\\" and \\\"AI matching\\\" are features—but your hosts don't care about features. They care about: \\\"I spend 30 minutes instead of 4 hours finding guests\\\" or \\\"My episodes with matched guests get 40% more engagement\\\" or \\\"I finally get guests who actually fit my show.\\\"\",\"examples\":[\"Instead of: 'We use AI to match based on content and audience' → Try: 'Hosts tell us they go from reviewing 50 pitches to 5 qualified matches per week—saving 3 hours of vetting time'\",\"Instead of: 'Proprietary models filter out bad fits' → Try: 'We predict which guests will resonate with YOUR specific audience by analyzing what made your top 10 episodes successful'\",\"Instead of: 'Perfect guest' → Try: 'A guest who brings relevant expertise, has an audience that overlaps with yours, and has a track record of being great on podcasts'\"],\"conclusion\":\"Once you nail the specific transformation—the time saved, the quality metric, the outcome that matters—your differentiator becomes crystal clear and way more compelling. Let's dig into what actually happens for your best customers.\"}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2451,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":482,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
