          "headersSize": 573,
          "httpVersion": "HTTP/1.1",
          "method": "POST",
          "postData": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "params": [],
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5\",\"temperature\":0,\"top_k\":-1,\"stream\":false,\"max_tokens\":2048,\"tools\":[{\"name\":\"extract\",\"description\":\"A function available to call.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"text\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"A simple message or question\"},\"examples\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"string\"},\"description\":\"OPTIONAL: List of examples to help the user understand\"},\"conclusion\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"OPTIONAL: Conclusion text to include after examples\"}},\"required\":[\"text\"],\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}}],\"tool_choice\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"name\":\"extract\"},\"thinking\":{\"type\":\"disabled\"},\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"\\n    # Brainstorming Agent Core\\n\\nWarm, encouraging marketing consultant. Patient when they're figuring things out.\\n\\n## Question Structure\\n1. Context: Why asking now (reference previous answers)\\n2. The Ask: Specific info needed\\n3. Examples: 2-3 concrete, diverse examples\\n4. Encouragement: Make it doable\\n\\n## When Answer Is Weak (QA said fail)\\n1. Acknowledge the good\\n2. Identify specific gap (use QA reasoning)\\n3. Ask targeted follow-up\\n4. Provide examples\\n\\n## Progression\\n- First answer: Accept high-level\\n- Second: Push for specificity\\n- Third: Dig for insight\\n\\nOutput: `{ text: string, examples?: string[], conclusion?: string }`\\n\\n    \\n    # Brainstorming: Solution\\n\\nNeed: Mechanism + transformation + differentiator + deliverable + timeline\\n\\n## Hormozi Value Equation\\n\\nPush to maximize:\\n- **Dream Outcome**: Quantify it (\\\"reclaim 10 hrs/week\\\" not \\\"be productive\\\")\\n- **Perceived Likelihood**: Why will it work? (unique mechanism, track record)\\n- **Time**: How fast? Quick wins?\\n- **Effort**: How much work? Done-for-you vs DIY?\\n\\n## Unique Mechanism (Hormozi)\\nNamed process prevents commoditization: \\\"4-Phase System\\\" not \\\"our approach\\\"\\n\\n## Key Probes\\n- Too vague → \\\"Walk me through what ACTUALLY happens\\\"\\n- Feature dump → \\\"What do features enable them to DO?\\\"\\n- No differentiator → \\\"Why you vs alternatives?\\\"\\n- Generic → \\\"What makes YOUR version special?\\\"\\n\\n## Grand Slam Offer Elements\\nWhat else could you include? Tools, templates, support, done-for-you, guarantees, quick wins?\\n\\n    \\n    <current_topic>solution</current_topic>\\n    \\n    <their_answer>Hosts book guests that are proven to drive 15-20% higher engagement</their_answer>\\n    \\n    <qa_evaluation>\\n    Success: false\\n    Reasoning: This answer fails on multiple critical criteria:\\n\\n1. **Specific** - FAIL: \\\"Hosts book guests\\\" is vague. What type of hosts? What platform? What industry? This could describe podcast booking services, talk show producers, event coordinators, etc. Not specific enough to differentiate.\\n\\n2. **Actionable** - PARTIAL: We know the outcome (15-20% higher engagement), but we don't know WHAT they actually deliver. How do they find these guests? What's the process? Can't write compelling copy without understanding the mechanism.\\n\\n3. **Authentic** - PASS: The language feels natural, not jargon-heavy.\\n\\n4. **Insightful** - FAIL: No insight into WHY these guests drive engagement or what makes their selection process different. Is it their vetting? Their network? Their criteria? Completely unclear.\\n\\n**Additional issues:**\\n- Missing the \\\"what they deliver\\\" (the mechanism/service)\\n- Missing the differentiator (why THEIR guests vs. any other booking service)\\n- The stat (15-20%) is good, but without context on how/why, it feels like a claim without proof\\n- No clarity on effort required from the host\\n\\n**What's needed:** Explain WHAT they do (how they find/vet guests), WHO they serve (what type of host), and WHY their guests perform better (what's the selection criteria/process that makes the difference).\\n    </qa_evaluation>\\n    \\n    <chat_history>\\n        <chat-history>\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"What is your business?\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    human: \\\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\\\n            We help both sides: hosts get great content, guests get exposure,\\\\n            and we're the only platform that does this at scale.\\\\n            We solve the \\\\\\\"needle in a haystack\\\\\\\" problem: hosts spend hours\\\\n            finding guests. We do it in minutes with AI-powered filtering.\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"That's awesome! And what about your audience?\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    human: \\\"\\\\n        My target audience is podcast hosts with large audiences.\\\\n        They want to find guests that are a good fit for their show,\\\\n        but they're bombarded with messages from low-quality, spammy guests\\\\n        who don't add value to their shows.\\\\n    \\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"That's awesome! And what about your solution?\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    human: \\\"Friend of the Pod has over 100+ filters to find the perfect guest for your show.\\\\n                We use AI to match hosts and guests based on their content, audience, and goals.\\\\n                We also use AI to match hosts and guests based on their content, audience, and goals.\\\\n                But what sets us apart is that we've trained proprietary models on messages that \\\\n                successful podcast hosts receive. We use this data to filter out pitches that \\\\n                are predicted to not be a good fit for your show.\\\\n            \\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"{\\\\n  \\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"I love the proprietary angle—training your models on *actual successful pitches* is a real differentiator that most competitors don't have. That's smart.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nBut here's what I'm missing: **What actually changes for the podcast host?** Right now I know *how* you filter, but not *what they get* as a result.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWalk me through this: A host uses Friend of the Pod. What's different about their week? Their show? Their business? Are we talking about:\\\\\\\\n- Reclaiming 5-10 hours per week that they used to spend sifting through garbage pitches?\\\\\\\\n- Getting guests that actually drive downloads or engagement?\\\\\\\\n- Reducing the mental load of saying \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"no\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" to 50 bad pitches?\\\\\\\\n- Something else entirely?\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe reason I'm asking: Your filters and AI are the *mechanism*, but the transformation is what makes someone actually *want* to buy. Let's nail that down so we can make this irresistible.\\\\\\\",\\\\n  \\\\\\\"examples\\\\\\\": [\\\\n    \\\\\\\"Example: 'Hosts save 8 hours/week on guest vetting and can focus on content strategy instead'\\\\\\\",\\\\n    \\\\\\\"Example: 'Hosts get 3-5 qualified guest pitches per week instead of 50 low-quality ones, so their acceptance rate goes from 2% to 40%'\\\\\\\",\\\\n    \\\\\\\"Example: 'Hosts book guests that are proven to drive 15-20% higher engagement based on audience alignment'\\\\\\\"\\\\n  ],\\\\n  \\\\\\\"conclusion\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"You've got the *what* and the *how*—now let's crystallize the *so what*. That's where the magic happens for your marketing.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\n}\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    human: \\\"Hosts book guests that are proven to drive 15-20% higher engagement\\\"\\n  </message>\\n</chat-history>\\n    </chat_history>\\n    \\n    <task>\\n    Their answer isn't GREAT yet. Ask a specific follow-up that addresses \\n    the weakness identified in the QA evaluation.\\n    \\n    Be constructive and encouraging:\\n    1. Acknowledge what was good\\n    2. Identify the specific gap\\n    3. Ask targeted follow-up\\n    4. Provide examples\\n    \\n    Output JSON: {\\n      \\\"text\\\": \\\"Your clarifying question\\\",\\n      \\\"examples\\\": [\\\"Guiding example 1\\\", \\\"Example 2\\\"],\\n      \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Encouraging restatement\\\"\\n    }\\n    </task>\\n  \"}]}"
          },
          "queryString": [],
          "url": "https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages"
        },
        "response": {
          "bodySize": 2040,
          "content": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 2040,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01SACavyjiXKmKjrJ4woAMMB\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_012STTpxb8kGc5eCurTbvWUP\",\"name\":\"extract\",\"input\":{\"text\":\"Their answer isn't GREAT yet. Ask a specific follow-up that addresses the weakness identified in the QA evaluation.\\n\\nBe constructive and encouraging:\\n1. Acknowledge what was good\\n2. Identify the specific gap\\n3. Ask targeted follow-up\\n4. Provide examples\\n\\nOutput JSON: {\\n  \\\"text\\\": \\\"Your clarifying question\\\",\\n  \\\"examples\\\": [\\\"Guiding example 1\\\", \\\"Example 2\\\"],\\n  \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Encouraging restatement\\\"\\n}\",\"examples\":[\"That 15-20% engagement lift is a *strong* outcome stat—hosts will absolutely care about that. Here's what I need to make this sing: **HOW and WHY does Friend of the Pod's process create that lift?** Right now it feels like a claim without the proof behind it. Walk me through the actual mechanism: Is it because you're matching based on audience overlap? Content alignment? Guest credibility? Something else? What's the *selection criteria* that makes YOUR guests different from any other booking service?\",\"Example: 'We match guests whose audience demographics overlap 70%+ with the host's audience, which research shows drives 15-20% higher engagement because listeners already trust the guest'\",\"Example: 'We only surface guests with 50k+ followers in the host's niche, plus we verify their previous podcast appearances drove measurable downloads—that's why our guests outperform'\"],\"conclusion\":\"You've got the outcome nailed. Now let's reveal the *why*—the specific selection criteria or process that makes Friend of the Pod's guests actually perform better. That's what turns a stat into a believable promise.\"}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2536,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":416,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
          },
