        "response": {
          "bodySize": 2292,
          "content": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 2292,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01TmYkKFdHuKvQ6rbzzNjqEu\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01DGCsYvmDGQCYLnCdwPJwTT\",\"name\":\"extract\",\"input\":{\"text\":\"You've got a really solid product here—AI-powered matching that saves hosts hours. That's genuinely valuable. But here's the thing: podcast hosts are skeptical. They get pitched constantly. So they need to believe this actually works before they commit.\\n\\nLet's talk social proof. Right now you don't have testimonials yet, which is totally normal for early-stage. But you've got other credibility levers we can pull.\\n\\nA few questions to get us started:\\n\\n**What's your background?** Have you been in podcasting, tech, or both? Any wins or transformations in your own life that led to this idea?\\n\\n**Early traction?** Even if it's small—beta users, friends who've tested it, podcasters who've given feedback—that counts. How many people have actually used Friend of the Pod?\\n\\n**Your process?** You mentioned training proprietary models on successful host messages. That's interesting. Can you quantify that? Like \\\"analyzed 10,000+ successful pitches\\\" or \\\"trained on data from top 500 podcasts\\\"?\\n\\nHere's why I'm asking: hosts don't need a celebrity endorsement. They need to know *someone like them* has tried this and it worked. That could be you, a beta user, or even the volume/rigor of your research.\",\"examples\":[\"Founder story: \\\"I spent 40 hours/month finding guests for my own show. Built this to solve my own problem. Now I do it in 15 minutes.\\\"\",\"Research credibility: \\\"Analyzed 15,000+ podcast pitches to identify what makes a guest 'good fit.' Found 7 patterns that predict host engagement.\\\"\",\"Early user proof: \\\"Beta tested with 50 podcast hosts. Average time to find guest dropped from 3 hours to 12 minutes. 92% said they'd use it again.\\\"\"],\"conclusion\":\"You've got the product. Now let's find the story that makes hosts believe it actually works. What resonates most with you?\"}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2237,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":499,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
