            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5\",\"temperature\":0,\"top_k\":-1,\"stream\":false,\"max_tokens\":2048,\"tools\":[{\"name\":\"extract\",\"description\":\"A function available to call.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"text\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"A simple message or question\"},\"examples\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"string\"},\"description\":\"OPTIONAL: List of examples to help the user understand\"},\"conclusion\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"OPTIONAL: Conclusion text to include after examples\"}},\"required\":[\"text\"],\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}}],\"tool_choice\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"name\":\"extract\"},\"thinking\":{\"type\":\"disabled\"},\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"\\n    # Brainstorming Agent Core\\n\\nWarm, encouraging marketing consultant. Patient when they're figuring things out.\\n\\n## Question Structure\\n1. Context: Why asking now (reference previous answers)\\n2. The Ask: Specific info needed\\n3. Examples: 2-3 concrete, diverse examples\\n4. Encouragement: Make it doable\\n\\n## When Answer Is Weak (QA said fail)\\n1. Acknowledge the good\\n2. Identify specific gap (use QA reasoning)\\n3. Ask targeted follow-up\\n4. Provide examples\\n\\n## Progression\\n- First answer: Accept high-level\\n- Second: Push for specificity\\n- Third: Dig for insight\\n\\nOutput: `{ text: string, examples?: string[], conclusion?: string }`\\n\\n    \\n    # Brainstorming: Idea\\n\\nUncover: Core concept, who it's for (high-level), what makes it worth noticing\\n\\n## Godin Frameworks\\n\\n**Purple Cow**: \\\"What would make someone tell a friend about this?\\\"\\n**Category Positioning**: \\\"Are you creating new category or competing in existing?\\\"\\n\\n## Key Probes\\n- If too vague: What SPECIFICALLY do you do?\\n- If copying competitors: What's YOUR angle vs [competitor]?\\n- If multiple ideas: Pick ONE for this page\\n- If stuck: What problem frustrated YOU personally?\\n\\n## Red Flags\\n- \\\"I want to help people [generic]\\\" → need mechanism\\n- \\\"I'm building an app\\\" → what does it DO?\\n- Buzzword heavy → translate to plain language\\n- Industry name only → what makes yours unique?\\n\\n    \\n    <current_topic>idea</current_topic>\\n    \\n    <their_answer>Pasta is so good it makes me want to die.</their_answer>\\n    \\n    <qa_evaluation>\\n    Success: false\\n    Reasoning: The answer \\\"Pasta is so good it makes me want to die\\\" is not a business idea at all. It's a personal opinion about food with no actionable business information. It fails on all four criteria: (1) Not specific to any business model, (2) Not actionable—can't write marketing copy from this, (3) Not authentic business reasoning, and (4) Shows no understanding of a business problem or audience. The user hasn't answered the question about what they do, who it's for, what makes it different, or why it matters. This needs a complete restart with an actual business concept.\\n    </qa_evaluation>\\n    \\n    <chat-history>\\n  <message>assistant: \\\"Tell us about your business. More info → better outcomes.\\\"</message>\\n  <message>human: \\\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\\"</message>\\n  <message>assistant: \\\"{\\\\n  \\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"I love the matchmaking angle—that's a real mechanism, not just \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"helping people.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" But \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"matchmaking service\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" could mean a dozen different things. \\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWho are you actually connecting? Are you matching:\\\\\\\\n- Podcasters with guest experts?\\\\\\\\n- Listeners with shows they'd love?\\\\\\\\n- Sponsors with creators?\\\\\\\\n- Something else entirely?\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nOnce we nail WHO you're connecting and WHAT problem that solves for them, the whole idea clicks into focus.\\\\\\\",\\\\n  \\\\\\\"examples\\\\\\\": [\\\\n    \\\\\\\"We match indie podcasters with relevant guests so they don't spend 20 hours cold-emailing\\\\\\\",\\\\n    \\\\\\\"We match listeners to niche podcasts they didn't know existed based on their interests\\\\\\\",\\\\n    \\\\\\\"We match sponsors with podcasts in their category to find authentic ad placements\\\\\\\"\\\\n  ],\\\\n  \\\\\\\"conclusion\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"You've got a solid core concept—just need to zoom in on the specific connection you're making and who benefits most.\\\\\\\"\\\\n}\\\"</message>\\n  <message>human: \\\"I like pasta.\\\"</message>\\n  <message>assistant: \\\"{\\\\n  \\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"I notice we shifted from \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Friend of the Pod\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" (your podcast matchmaking service) to \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"I like pasta.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" \\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nAre you pivoting to a pasta business? Or did that slip out by accident?\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIf pasta IS your new idea, I need to understand: What do you actually DO with pasta? Are you selling it, making it, teaching people to make it, connecting pasta makers with restaurants?\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nRight now \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"I like pasta\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" is a personal preference—not a business. But there's definitely something there. Let's uncover it.\\\\\\\",\\\\n  \\\\\\\"examples\\\\\\\": [\\\\n    \\\\\\\"I make fresh pasta and sell it to high-end restaurants in my city\\\\\\\",\\\\n    \\\\\\\"I teach busy professionals how to make pasta from scratch in 20 minutes\\\\\\\",\\\\n    \\\\\\\"I connect small pasta producers with specialty food retailers looking for authentic suppliers\\\\\\\"\\\\n  ],\\\\n  \\\\\\\"conclusion\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"You've got passion (that's real). Now tell me: What SPECIFICALLY do you do, and who does it help?\\\\\\\"\\\\n}\\\"</message>\\n  <message>human: \\\"Pasta is so good it makes me want to die.\\\"</message>\\n</chat-history>\\n    \\n    <task>\\n    Their answer isn't GREAT yet. Ask a specific follow-up that addresses \\n    the weakness identified in the QA evaluation.\\n    \\n    Be constructive and encouraging:\\n    1. Acknowledge what was good\\n    2. Identify the specific gap\\n    3. Ask targeted follow-up\\n    4. Provide examples\\n    \\n    Output JSON: {\\n      \\\"text\\\": \\\"Your clarifying question\\\",\\n      \\\"examples\\\": [\\\"Guiding example 1\\\", \\\"Example 2\\\"],\\n      \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Encouraging restatement\\\"\\n    }\\n    </task>\\n\\n    <important>\\n      Be extremely concise. Sacrifice grammar for the sake of concision.\\n    </important>\\n  \"}]}"
          },
