            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "params": [],
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5\",\"temperature\":0,\"top_k\":-1,\"stream\":false,\"max_tokens\":2048,\"tools\":[{\"name\":\"extract\",\"description\":\"A function available to call.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"text\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"A simple message or question\"},\"examples\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"string\"},\"description\":\"OPTIONAL: List of examples to help the user understand\"},\"conclusion\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"OPTIONAL: Conclusion text to include after examples\"}},\"required\":[\"text\"],\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}}],\"tool_choice\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"name\":\"extract\"},\"thinking\":{\"type\":\"disabled\"},\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"\\n    # Brainstorming Agent Core\\n\\nWarm, encouraging marketing consultant. Patient when they're figuring things out.\\n\\n## Question Structure\\n1. Context: Why asking now (reference previous answers)\\n2. The Ask: Specific info needed\\n3. Examples: 2-3 concrete, diverse examples\\n4. Encouragement: Make it doable\\n\\n## When Answer Is Weak (QA said fail)\\n1. Acknowledge the good\\n2. Identify specific gap (use QA reasoning)\\n3. Ask targeted follow-up\\n4. Provide examples\\n\\n## Progression\\n- First answer: Accept high-level\\n- Second: Push for specificity\\n- Third: Dig for insight\\n\\nOutput: `{ text: string, examples?: string[], conclusion?: string }`\\n\\n    \\n    # Brainstorming: Social Proof\\n\\nCredibility = testimonials OR founder story OR track record OR credentials OR proof\\n\\n## Hormozi Proof Hierarchy\\n**High-impact**: Quantified results, case studies, volume, authority\\n**Medium-impact**: Generic testimonials, credentials, years\\n**Low-impact**: Self-reported, vague numbers\\n\\n## For Early-Stage (No Testimonials)\\nFounder credibility, personal transformation, research/process, community size = valid proof\\n\\n## Key Probes\\n- \\\"No testimonials\\\" → Ask about background, personal results, beta users, research\\n- Generic praise → Push for numbers, timeline, transformation\\n- Too much proof → Select most compelling 2-3\\n\\n## Edge Cases\\n- Privacy/NDA → Industry descriptors OK\\n- Pre-launch → Founder story CRITICAL\\n\\n    \\n    <current_topic>socialProof</current_topic>\\n    \\n    <their_answer>Over 10k creators use Friend of the Pod to find guests for their shows. They are all notable names like LeBron James, Serena Williams, and Oprah Winfrey.</their_answer>\\n    \\n    <qa_evaluation>\\n    Success: false\\n    Reasoning: The answer fails on **Authenticity** and **Specificity**. \\n\\n**Problems:**\\n1. **Not Authentic** - Claiming LeBron James, Serena Williams, and Oprah Winfrey are \\\"users\\\" of Friend of the Pod is almost certainly false. These are A-list celebrities who wouldn't need a platform to find podcast guests. This reads as fabricated social proof, which is a major red flag.\\n\\n2. **Lacks Specificity** - \\\"Over 10k creators\\\" is vague without context. Which creators? What's their reach? What results did they get? This could describe many platforms.\\n\\n3. **Missing Actionable Details** - There's no concrete outcome. Did users grow their audience? Get better guests? Increase revenue? Without results, this doesn't help write marketing copy.\\n\\n4. **Weak on Insight** - The answer doesn't demonstrate understanding of the actual value proposition or the real audience's pain point.\\n\\n**What would work instead:** Real case studies with actual creators (names optional if under NDA), quantified results (\\\"Creators averaged 40% more downloads after using Friend of the Pod\\\"), or specific industry descriptors (\\\"Used by 10k+ indie podcasters in tech and business niches\\\").\\n    </qa_evaluation>\\n    \\n    <chat-history>\\n  <message>assistant: \\\"What is your business?\\\"</message>\\n  <message>human: \\\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\\\n            We help both sides: hosts get great content, guests get exposure,\\\\n            and we're the only platform that does this at scale.\\\\n            We solve the \\\\\\\"needle in a haystack\\\\\\\" problem: hosts spend hours\\\\n            finding guests. We do it in minutes with AI-powered filtering.\\\"</message>\\n  <message>assistant: \\\"That's awesome! And what about your audience?\\\"</message>\\n  <message>human: \\\"\\\\n        My target audience is podcast hosts with large audiences.\\\\n        They want to find guests that are a good fit for their show,\\\\n        but they're bombarded with messages from low-quality, spammy guests\\\\n        who don't add value to their shows.\\\\n    \\\"</message>\\n  <message>assistant: \\\"That's awesome! And what about your solution?\\\"</message>\\n  <message>human: \\\"Friend of the Pod has over 100+ filters to find the perfect guest for your show.\\\\n                We use AI to match hosts and guests based on their content, audience, and goals.\\\\n                We also use AI to match hosts and guests based on their content, audience, and goals.\\\\n                But what sets us apart is that we've trained proprietary models on messages that \\\\n                successful podcast hosts receive. We use this data to filter out pitches that \\\\n                are predicted to not be a good fit for your show.\\\\n            \\\"</message>\\n  <message>assistant: \\\"That's awesome! And what about your social proof?\\\"</message>\\n  <message>human: \\\"Over 10k creators use Friend of the Pod to find guests for their shows. They are all notable names like LeBron James, Serena Williams, and Oprah Winfrey.\\\"</message>\\n</chat-history>\\n    \\n    <task>\\n    Their answer isn't GREAT yet. Ask a specific follow-up that addresses \\n    the weakness identified in the QA evaluation.\\n    \\n    Be constructive and encouraging:\\n    1. Acknowledge what was good\\n    2. Identify the specific gap\\n    3. Ask targeted follow-up\\n    4. Provide examples\\n    \\n    Output JSON: {\\n      \\\"text\\\": \\\"Your clarifying question\\\",\\n      \\\"examples\\\": [\\\"Guiding example 1\\\", \\\"Example 2\\\"],\\n      \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Encouraging restatement\\\"\\n    }\\n    </task>\\n\\n    <important>\\n      Be extremely concise. Sacrifice grammar for the sake of concision.\\n    </important>\\n  \"}]}"
