          "bodySize": 1441,
          "content": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 1441,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01FBiUsV7yTHsPq9MUzM3Yy2\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01QtSZF33JiCAbFyDmdKucR2\",\"name\":\"extract\",\"input\":{\"text\":\"I love that you have 10k+ creators using Friend of the Pod—that's real scale! But here's the thing: those celebrity names (LeBron, Serena, Oprah) don't quite ring true for a podcast guest-matching platform. They'd likely have teams handling that already.\\n\\nLet's dig into what's *actually* happening with your real users. What concrete results are your creators seeing? And who are they really—what niches or show types are they in?\",\"examples\":[\"A creator in the business podcast space went from 2 guest pitches/week to 15 qualified ones, boosting downloads 35%\",\"Tech podcast hosts in the 50k-500k listener range are your sweet spot—they're the ones actively using the platform to scale\",\"Real case: Host found 3 guests in 10 minutes instead of 5 hours of manual outreach, leading to 2 viral episodes\"],\"conclusion\":\"You've got the numbers. Now let's make them *believable* by showing the actual transformation your creators experience. That's what sells.\"}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2080,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":293,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
